above.
Retention
We have record retention processes designed to retain personal information for no longer than necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Notice or as otherwise required to meet valid legal or business requirements in accordance with applicablelaw.
Transfers of Personal Information
We and our service providers (including affiliates and subsidiaries) may access, store and otherwise process personal information outside of Canada, including in the United States and other foreign jurisdictions. We and our service providers may disclose your personal information if required or permitted by applicable law or legal process, which may include lawful access by foreign courts, law enforcement or other government authorities in the jurisdictions in which we or our service providers operate. For information about our practices with respect to the use of service providers outside of Canada, please contact our Privacy Officer at
batprivacyrequests@hearst.com
.
